Dear Customers

We will be doing our first ever price adjustment in the new year.
We do know that this can be a sensitive topic and will therefore do our very best to be
forthcoming and informative about the reasons and the obligations that relates to the price
adjustment.

There are three primary reasons for the price adjustment:
Wage increases here at Albatross, higher rent and increased cost of produce.

Wages
We have a progressive wage program for all staff at Albatross. Predictable and Automatic.
This means that each staff member gets at least two wage increases per year: One for seniority,
and one as an "inflation equalizer".
The "inflation equalizer" is put in place to ensure that our staffs' relative purchasing power does
not decrease.

Example:
On January 1st 2020 the minimum wage (Mindestlohn) goes up with 1,7%. Consequently all
wages at Albatross will go up with 1,7%. In addition to that each staff member will get an
increase to their wage for each full year of employment with us.
The lowest wage here at Albatross is 15,4% higher than the minimum wage.

Rent
We signed our contract here on Graefestrasse in 2018. We pay circa €21/square meter.
Our contract includes progressive rent increases every year. This year our rent will go up with
3%. Cost of Produce
The cost of produce goes up. Always.
The vast majority of the produce we use is organic and regional.

Our flour comes from Paulicks Mühle in Spreewald.
Our butter comes from Gläserne Molkerei in Spreewald.
Almost all our fresh produce comes from Terra Naturkost in Berlin.

We are proud of our suppliers and are happy to be working with companies that work with a
high degree of responsibility and transparency on conditions for their staff, their animals, and
our environment.

Should you have any questions or be interested in specific information relating to this topic, then
please do not hesitate to get in touch.
You can reach us here: info@albatrossberlin.com

All the best, The Albas
